A: Our lumbar pillow features two adjustable shoulder straps that can accommodate different types of seats, ensuring it stays in place. Q: Does it help alleviate lower back pain? A: When leaning against the cushion, the premium memory foam filling can absorb some pressure, thereby reducing strain on the spine and muscles, which helps alleviate back discomfort. Q: Is it suitable for use in a car? A: This lumbar support pillow is suitable for car seats and can help relieve pain from prolonged sitting. However, if your car seat is shallow, the pillow will take up some of your seat space to provide adequate back support, which is unavoidable. How to reset? (1) [Clear the pairing information on your phone]: Go to Settings-Bluetooth to delete the BTR7 pairing information and reconnect it to BTR7 Bluetooth amps. (2) [Clear the pairing information on BTR7]: When it is on, hold both the volume- and volume+ buttons at the same time for about 5s. (3) [Reset operation]: Click the power button and the volume - button at the same time. Q2: How to use the BTR7 amplifier as a USB DAC for mobile phones? [Android phone] Use the Type-C to Type-C cable included in the package to connect the BTR7 to your mobile phone. Play music to directly enjoy high-quality music. Note: If there is no sound after connecting, you need to pay attention to the following points: (1) Settings on apps, such as FiiO Music, there is a USB output that needs to be enabled, but some devices will have sound only with the USB output turned off. (2) Please check if the USB debugging is enabled in developer mode. You may need to open "Developer Options" in "Other Advanced Settings", and then enable the "USB Debugging" or "OTG" function. (3) Please confirm whether the cable is FiiO's type C to type C cable, whether the cable is reversed as there is a direction indication. (4) After the above settings are completed, you can try to re-plug the data cable, or play the track, play another track to make sure whether it is a hardware or software issue. If your issue remains, please contact our support team by google "fiio" to confirm whether it needs to be returned. When connecting BTR7 amplifier to Android mobile phone which supports Aptx adaptive Bluetooth codec, the default Bluetooth codec will be Aptx adaptive. If you would like to use other Bluetooth codec(Like LDAC), please follow this steps for help: 1. Enter FiiO Control app-BTR7-Status. 2. Click "select Bluetooth code". 3. Find the rim seam where two edges of front bumper and back cover meet and take the front and the back apart. Q: What’s the use of the rim seam where two edges meet? A: It’s designed for letting the front bumper properly and snugly nestled in the back cover, to provide best possible protection against drops. Step2: Install the hard PC front frame. Please set the top side (front camera side) around the iPhone first, and then attach the bottom side (charging port side). ** Top to bottom installation is crucial for proper fitting of the front piece. DO NOT install the front piece from bottom to top. Q: Can I install the front piece from the bottom side to the top side? A: No! Our phone case is not designed to be installed in this order of steps. You will be unable to install the front bumper starting from the bottom side, finishing with the top side. You must follow the order of steps through our instructions. Step3: Install the soft TPU back cover. Snap the front piece tightly into place with the back cover. Q: I feel it is a little tight to install the back cover. Is it normal? A: Yes,it is normal. column4: Previous page Next page 1 Compact Power 2 MultiProtect 3 Scratch Protection Why is my power bank providing fewer charges than expected? The capacity reduction during charging is due to a 30% to 45% energy loss in the battery cells and conversion circuitry. Therefore, a fully charged Anker A1610 Battery (PowerCore 5K) offers an estimated 2,750mAh~3,250mAhto power devices. How can I estimate the number of charges for my device? To estimate charging cycles, use these formula:(Power Bank Capacity × 0.5) ÷ Device Battery Capacity ˜ Number of Charges. For instance, charging a 3,000mAh device using a 5,000mAh Wireless power bank would offer approximately 0.83 charges. Why does charging stop at 80%? Your iPhone may automatically stop charging at 80% to protect its battery from overheating, as part of iOS 17's thermal management strategy. Charging will resume once the device cools down. Moving it to a cooler spot can help speed up this process. Why is my phone overheating? It's normal for devices to warm up slightly during wireless charging, particularly with heavy use like extensive gaming or streaming. Rest assured, this device meets international safety standards for safe operation.
